      <arrangement id="aspace_458c9fe2d72bb690fb72064252b29a44">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into eleven series: I. Correspondence, 1915-1975. II. Writings, 1931-1968. III. Research Files, 1851-1978. IV. Writings of Others, 1938-1975. V. Personal Papers, 1888-1975. VI. Professional Papers, 1932-1979. VII. Photographs and Microfilm, circa 1920-1941, undated. VII. Printed Material, circa 1890-1975. VIII. Audiovisual Material, 1963-1985. IX. Realia, undated. X. Material Removed From Books, circa 1960-1975.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_d45620e2f406f42b82a7f1b81abe2291">
         <head>Norman Holmes Pearson (1909-1975)</head>
         <p>Norman Holmes Pearson (Yale 1932), professor of English and American Studies at Yale University and officer in the Office of Strategic Services during the Second World War. Pearson collaborated with curator Donald Gallup to develop the Yale Collection of American Literature, playing an instrumental role in the acquisition of the papers of H.D. and Bryher.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_e4dd246afef1a42cbcd588e50d069dcf">
